1
00:00:50,366 --> 00:00:53,154
WOMAN: For as long
as I could remember,

2
00:00:53,254 --> 00:00:55,605
the four of us shared everything.

3
00:00:55,705 --> 00:00:57,969
Stories...

4
00:00:58,141 --> 00:01:00,439
...secrets...

5
00:01:00,610 --> 00:01:02,840
...laughter...

6
00:01:03,346 --> 00:01:05,346
...broken hearts.

7
00:01:08,351 --> 00:01:11,341
So when we found a
pair of pants that,

8
00:01:11,441 --> 00:01:14,961
by some miracle, fit
each of us perfectly...

9
00:01:15,158 --> 00:01:20,118
...we took it on faith they'd come
into our lives for a reason.

10
00:01:25,568 --> 00:01:27,704
That summer and the
two that followed...

11
00:01:27,804 --> 00:01:31,724
...the pants had the magic
of keeping us together.

12
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:36,410
No matter where they found us.

13
00:01:37,380 --> 00:01:38,715
[BLOWS WHISTLE]

14
00:01:38,815 --> 00:01:40,815
BRIDGET: Bring it in.

15
00:01:41,918 --> 00:01:42,918
CARMEN:

16
00:01:43,018 --> 00:01:45,898
They saw us through
times of love...

17
00:01:55,265 --> 00:01:57,265
...times of loss...

18
00:02:08,077 --> 00:02:11,757
MAN: Congratulations.
- ... and times of change.

19
00:02:18,688 --> 00:02:23,248
And those moments where you
feel your life just lift up...

20
00:02:23,359 --> 00:02:25,359
...and take off.

21
00:02:28,898 --> 00:02:29,999
Let go.

22
00:02:30,099 --> 00:02:32,256
That fall when we left
for college, I watched...

23
00:02:32,356 --> 00:02:34,237
each of my friends
settle into a new life.

24
00:02:34,337 --> 00:02:37,238
Cut.
- Tibby was at NYU.

25
00:02:39,475 --> 00:02:42,178
Bridget made the
soccer team at Brown.

26
00:02:42,278 --> 00:02:43,513
[WHISTLE BLOWS]...

27
00:02:43,613 --> 00:02:45,613
[CROWD CHEERING]

28
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:53,746
And Lena? She was
on scholarship...

29
00:02:53,846 --> 00:02:56,486
at Rhode Island School of Design.

30
00:03:03,099 --> 00:03:04,976
They made it look so easy,

31
00:03:05,076 --> 00:03:08,138
fitting right in and
making new friends...

32
00:03:08,238 --> 00:03:11,020
...while I was at Yale just waiting...

33
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:13,977
for something to feel
real or familiar.

34
00:03:14,077 --> 00:03:17,340
I was lost without
them, especially when...

35
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:20,480
it felt like my mom
was moving on too.

36
00:03:29,525 --> 00:03:33,765
I believed that the Sisterhood
could survive anything.

37
00:03:34,430 --> 00:03:36,633
But maybe the pants had done...

38
00:03:36,733 --> 00:03:39,736
just about all a pair
of pants could do...

39
00:03:39,836 --> 00:03:43,363
...and the rest
we had to learn on our own.

40
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:47,970
How to become ourselves
without losing each other.

41
00:03:57,020 --> 00:04:00,888
[MAN SPEAKING IN
FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

42
00:04:55,278 --> 00:04:57,278
LENA: Kostos?

43
00:05:06,055 --> 00:05:08,182
I'm so sorry, Lena.

44
00:05:10,693 --> 00:05:13,413
I know how much
Bapi meant to you.

45
00:05:15,064 --> 00:05:17,064
It's good to see you.

46
00:05:20,069 --> 00:05:22,705
These past few months have just...
- Lena.

47
00:05:22,805 --> 00:05:24,805
I've missed you.

48
00:05:25,508 --> 00:05:27,176
I only broke up with you because...

49
00:05:27,276 --> 00:05:30,245
[SPEAKING IN GREEK]

50
00:05:34,617 --> 00:05:36,617
Lena...

51
00:05:36,819 --> 00:05:38,819
...this is Melia.

52
00:05:41,491 --> 00:05:43,491
My wife.

53
00:05:58,107 --> 00:06:01,338
WOMAN:
And treachery in me, your queen.

54
00:06:01,511 --> 00:06:03,379
Wait, Kostos got married?

55
00:06:03,479 --> 00:06:06,999
Yep. Apparently
there's a B-A-B-Y on the way.

56
00:06:07,116 --> 00:06:09,116
Oh, my God.

57
00:06:09,185 --> 00:06:10,594
I didn't get the whole story.

58
00:06:10,694 --> 00:06:12,455
You have to Heimlich
it out of Lena.

59
00:06:12,555 --> 00:06:14,357
Well, she must be devastated.

60
00:06:14,457 --> 00:06:15,909
Wait, why didn't she call me?

61
00:06:16,009 --> 00:06:17,927
I hardly hear from
her, or any of you.

62
00:06:18,027 --> 00:06:20,396
She was probably planning on
telling you when school's out.

63
00:06:20,496 --> 00:06:23,599
Listen, I gotta go.
I think I just found bliss.

64
00:06:23,699 --> 00:06:26,499
Love you.
- Okay, l... Love you too.

65
00:06:28,371 --> 00:06:30,931
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYS
O VER SPEAKERS]

66
00:06:32,008 --> 00:06:34,008
CARMEN: Here you go.

67
00:06:34,377 --> 00:06:36,112
Hold this.
- How was it?

68
00:06:36,212 --> 00:06:37,780
It was great. One of your best.

69
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:40,041
Excuse me. Out of the way.

70
00:06:43,519 --> 00:06:47,824
My God, there is nothing more
invigorating than a full house.

71
00:06:47,924 --> 00:06:50,460
Here, take it down.
I just want to get this dress off.

72
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:53,840
I can barely breathe.
Perfect. Thank you.

73
00:06:53,863 --> 00:06:55,863
You're welcome.

74
00:06:57,967 --> 00:07:00,947
These came for you
during intermission.

75
00:07:01,047 --> 00:07:02,009
Oh. Great.

76
00:07:02,109 --> 00:07:04,874
She's consistent. My mother sends
two dozen yellow roses...

77
00:07:04,974 --> 00:07:06,809
...every time she doesn't show up.

78
00:07:06,909 --> 00:07:08,478
Let's see.

79
00:07:08,578 --> 00:07:11,948
'Sorry I couldn't be there, darling.
See you in Vermont.' Of course.

80
00:07:12,048 --> 00:07:13,616
Have you ever been to Vermont?

81
00:07:13,716 --> 00:07:14,817
Vermont?
- Yeah.

82
00:07:14,917 --> 00:07:16,742
I'm doing an acting
internship at the

83
00:07:16,842 --> 00:07:18,921
Village Theater Arts
Festival this summer.

84
00:07:19,021 --> 00:07:22,158
My mom will have to go to that.
A lot of her friends will be in it.

85
00:07:22,258 --> 00:07:24,961
Professional actors.
We actually get to work with them.

86
00:07:25,061 --> 00:07:28,364
Hey, Carmen, they're always
looking for people backstage.

87
00:07:28,464 --> 00:07:30,767
I could pull a few strings
if you're interested.

88
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:33,859
Oh, wow. That's
really nice of you...

89
00:07:34,036 --> 00:07:36,973
...but I made plans to go home,
because my mom's pregnant...

90
00:07:37,073 --> 00:07:39,154
...and we're moving,
and my friends...

91
00:07:39,254 --> 00:07:40,943
would kill me if I wasn't home.

92
00:07:41,043 --> 00:07:43,843
But thank you.
- Yeah, I understand.

93
00:07:45,915 --> 00:07:47,915
Dad, I'm home.

94
00:07:54,757 --> 00:07:56,757
Dad?

95
00:07:58,427 --> 00:08:00,063
FATHER: Bridget.

96
00:08:00,163 --> 00:08:03,299
Hey, honey. I didn't expect you
home so soon.

97
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:05,629
I know, me either.

98
00:08:05,801 --> 00:08:07,996
You hungry? Want a slice?

99
00:08:08,171 --> 00:08:09,539
Favorite recipe.

100
00:08:09,639 --> 00:08:12,279
No, it's okay, I ate on the road.

101
00:08:13,643 --> 00:08:15,643
So how's school?

102
00:08:15,645 --> 00:08:18,637
Good. Yeah.

103
00:08:18,814 --> 00:08:20,894
How's everything with you?

104
00:08:21,050 --> 00:08:23,109
Good. You know, same.

105
00:08:23,286 --> 00:08:25,286
Yeah.

106
00:08:25,788 --> 00:08:27,813
Okay. Great.

107
00:08:29,292 --> 00:08:32,159
Um, I guess I'll go unpack.

108
00:08:34,096 --> 00:08:36,096
Get some rest.

109
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:49,610
Mom.

110
00:08:52,682 --> 00:08:54,517
Mom.

111
00:08:54,617 --> 00:08:55,718
CHRISTINA: What is it?

112
00:08:55,818 --> 00:08:57,818
CARMEN: Where's my stuff?

113
00:08:58,788 --> 00:09:00,703
We just wanted to get a jump-start...

114
00:09:00,803 --> 00:09:02,825
on all the packing.
It's gonna be fine.

115
00:09:02,925 --> 00:09:05,325
Here are your towels.
- Thanks.

116
00:09:05,461 --> 00:09:08,264
CHRISTINA:
David, is this the box you wanted?

117
00:09:08,364 --> 00:09:10,604
DAVID: Let me see it, honey.

118
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:13,300
Welcome home.

119
00:09:14,937 --> 00:09:17,707
I'm sorry I'm late, I'm sorry.
I didn't pack the boom box.

120
00:09:17,807 --> 00:09:21,087
But I'm here.
And it's so good to see you.

121
00:09:21,877 --> 00:09:24,013
It's been too long.
Your piercing closed up.

122
00:09:24,113 --> 00:09:26,649
I know, right? Cool in Bethesda,
passé in the Village.

123
00:09:26,749 --> 00:09:28,084
Here, hold this.

124
00:09:28,184 --> 00:09:29,952
Why are these open?
CARMEN: I got hungry.

125
00:09:30,052 --> 00:09:31,154
Hi, Bee.
- Carma.

126
00:09:31,254 --> 00:09:34,123
Wow, you came prepared.
- Well, it's all that theater work.

127
00:09:34,223 --> 00:09:35,224
Theater work? Acting?

128
00:09:35,324 --> 00:09:37,126
I always said you
were a drama queen.

129
00:09:37,226 --> 00:09:39,262
Thank you, but no.
It's behind-the-scenes.

130
00:09:39,362 --> 00:09:41,632
Does this mean you're
gonna be able to help...

131
00:09:41,732 --> 00:09:43,699
me with my screenplay
for summer school?

132
00:09:43,799 --> 00:09:45,101
Summer school?

133
00:09:45,201 --> 00:09:46,736
Well, yeah, I got an incomplete.

134
00:09:46,836 --> 00:09:48,809
I was supposed to write a romantic...

135
00:09:48,909 --> 00:09:50,773
comedy, but my
characters broke up.

136
00:09:50,873 --> 00:09:52,775
You're gonna be in
New York the summer?

137
00:09:52,875 --> 00:09:53,576
Yeah, it sucks.

138
00:09:53,676 --> 00:09:55,745
Brian will come visit
you every weekend.

139
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:58,114
Because the guy worships
the ground you walk on.

140
00:09:58,214 --> 00:10:00,249
Don't you just hate that in a guy?

141
00:10:00,349 --> 00:10:03,389
BRIDGET: Take these.
- Bee, be careful.

142
00:10:03,519 --> 00:10:04,754
If you fall, I'll laugh.

143
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:06,880
LENA: It always
makes me nervous...

144
00:10:06,980 --> 00:10:08,057
when she does this.

145
00:10:08,157 --> 00:10:10,157
Oh, my God.
- Oh.

146
00:10:13,929 --> 00:10:15,929
Piece of cake.

147
00:10:16,499 --> 00:10:16,764
CARMEN:

148
00:10:16,864 --> 00:10:18,701
We'll be like 85 climbing
up these stairs.

149
00:10:18,801 --> 00:10:21,137
You not gonna be able
to do that again.

150
00:10:21,237 --> 00:10:24,440
Okay, Tib, please come out
of downward dog.

151
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:27,304
TIBBY: Okay.
- Pants.

152
00:10:27,476 --> 00:10:30,240
Check. Junk food.

153
00:10:31,013 --> 00:10:32,348
LENA: Oh, wow.
CARMEN: Check.

154
00:10:32,448 --> 00:10:34,283
Have some chips.

155
00:10:34,383 --> 00:10:35,585
Cheesy '80s music, check.

156
00:10:35,685 --> 00:10:36,376
[C YNDI LAUPER'S 'GIRLS JUST

157
00:10:36,476 --> 00:10:37,353
WANNA HAVE FUN'
PLAYS ON STEREO]...

158
00:10:37,453 --> 00:10:39,139
I forgot. What do we do first?

159
00:10:39,239 --> 00:10:41,157
Carmen goes next
and she does the:

160
00:10:41,257 --> 00:10:42,864
'Blah, blah, blah, rules one, two,

161
00:10:42,964 --> 00:10:44,961
and three of the pants.
Blah, blah, blah.'

162
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:46,466
Prayer, and we hold hands.

163
00:10:46,566 --> 00:10:48,531
And then we all sit
around and pray.

164
00:10:48,631 --> 00:10:50,333
That's very sentimental, Tibby.

165
00:10:50,433 --> 00:10:52,290
I'm just saying. We've
been doing this...

166
00:10:52,390 --> 00:10:53,502
for a couple summers now.

167
00:10:53,602 --> 00:10:55,740
We don't need the ritual
every single time.

168
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,673
Why not? It's not
any less important.

169
00:10:57,773 --> 00:11:00,543
Okay, you guys, let's just keep
the same rotation. Okay?

170
00:11:00,643 --> 00:11:02,979
So, what, now you guys
don't care about it either?

171
00:11:03,079 --> 00:11:04,380
We care.

172
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:07,328
Carmen, we've done
this a million times.

173
00:11:07,428 --> 00:11:09,986
It's not that big of a deal anymore.

174
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:12,329
So if we just keep going
as usual, you have...

175
00:11:12,429 --> 00:11:14,223
them for a week and
you pass them on.

176
00:11:14,323 --> 00:11:15,005
TIBBY: Bee's next.

177
00:11:15,105 --> 00:11:16,559
LENA: Don't take
them on your digs...

178
00:11:16,659 --> 00:11:19,595
...with those corroded bones
and corpses.

179
00:11:19,695 --> 00:11:22,365
I'm sorry I'm not painting
in a studio all summer.

180
00:11:22,465 --> 00:11:24,806
Wait, what are you
guys talking about?

181
00:11:24,906 --> 00:11:26,869
Bones and studios, what is that?

182
00:11:26,969 --> 00:11:30,873
I got accepted into this
archaeological camp in Turkey...

183
00:11:30,973 --> 00:11:33,109
...so I'm gonna go
there for the summer.

184
00:11:33,209 --> 00:11:35,609
Didn't you get my e-mail?
- No.

185
00:11:35,778 --> 00:11:38,498
I'm taking a figure drawing class.

186
00:11:39,014 --> 00:11:41,014
Cool.

187
00:11:44,820 --> 00:11:47,620
What are your plans
for the summer?

188
00:11:48,491 --> 00:11:50,159
Um...

189
00:11:50,259 --> 00:11:52,259
I'm going to Vermont.

190
00:11:53,195 --> 00:11:54,997
Really?

191
00:11:55,097 --> 00:11:56,399
Yep.

192
00:11:56,499 --> 00:11:58,499
Vermont.

193
00:11:59,368 --> 00:12:01,298
Can't you take me
with you to RISD?

194
00:12:01,398 --> 00:12:03,272
I'll die of boredom here, I swear.

195
00:12:03,372 --> 00:12:05,074
Come on, I'm your sister.

196
00:12:05,174 --> 00:12:07,411
I thought you were
going back to Greece.

197
00:12:07,511 --> 00:12:08,511
Not until August.

198
00:12:08,611 --> 00:12:13,082
Oh, God. Okay, that reminds me.
What should I do about Kostos?

199
00:12:13,182 --> 00:12:14,784
What do you mean?

200
00:12:14,884 --> 00:12:17,253
You know, if I see
him, what do I say?

201
00:12:17,353 --> 00:12:19,353
Or do I not say anything?

202
00:12:19,488 --> 00:12:22,367
God, what if I see him with her and...

203
00:12:22,467 --> 00:12:25,987
she's, like, all out to
here and everything?

204
00:12:26,162 --> 00:12:28,162
I don't know.

205
00:12:28,164 --> 00:12:29,552
We agreed to see other people,

206
00:12:29,652 --> 00:12:31,567
so I knew there was
a possibility he'd...

207
00:12:31,667 --> 00:12:33,583
That he'd date someone,
not get her...

208
00:12:33,683 --> 00:12:35,237
pregnant and have to marry her.

209
00:12:35,337 --> 00:12:40,009
God, whatever. Just talk to him,
don't talk to him, I don't care.

210
00:12:40,109 --> 00:12:41,677
WOMAN:
Effie Kaligaris, we have to go.

211
00:12:41,777 --> 00:12:43,777
Yeah, coming.

212
00:12:44,413 --> 00:12:47,773
Hey, Mom, can we pick up Ashley
on the way?

213
00:13:31,927 --> 00:13:35,064
Why didn't you tell me
she'd been writing all these years?

214
00:13:35,164 --> 00:13:36,565
Where did you get these?

215
00:13:36,665 --> 00:13:38,665
Where you hid them.

216
00:13:41,136 --> 00:13:45,141
Your mother and I weren't on
speaking terms with Greta.

217
00:13:45,241 --> 00:13:47,576
It was in your best interest...
- My best interest?

218
00:13:47,676 --> 00:13:48,771
What, to make me think...

219
00:13:48,871 --> 00:13:50,379
my own grandmother
didn't love me?

220
00:13:50,479 --> 00:13:52,548
You had no right to do that to me.

221
00:13:52,648 --> 00:13:54,383
I had a right, Bridget.

222
00:13:54,483 --> 00:13:57,923
I'm your father.
It's my job to protect you.

223
00:13:58,287 --> 00:14:00,482
Protect me? From what?

224
00:14:00,656 --> 00:14:02,625
I can take care of myself, Dad.

225
00:14:02,725 --> 00:14:07,205
In case you hadn't noticed,
I've been doing it for years.

226
00:14:46,468 --> 00:14:49,828
Over there is the Ford Theater.
- Oh, cool.

227
00:14:54,543 --> 00:14:55,929
I'm so glad you
changed your mind.

228
00:14:56,029 --> 00:14:56,612
CARMEN: Me too.

229
00:14:56,712 --> 00:14:57,712
JULIA:

230
00:14:57,812 --> 00:14:59,582
Thank God for summer
theater, huh?

231
00:14:59,682 --> 00:15:03,709
Julia, Julia, Julia, darling.

232
00:15:03,886 --> 00:15:06,755
How nice to have you
back with us this season.

233
00:15:06,855 --> 00:15:08,591
JULIA: Thanks.
- How's your mother? Working?

234
00:15:08,691 --> 00:15:10,926
Of course. But she sends her love.

235
00:15:11,026 --> 00:15:13,995
Tell her love should not be sent.

236
00:15:14,163 --> 00:15:16,899
Carmen, this is Bill Kerr,
our brilliant director.

237
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:18,100
KERR: Uh-uh-uh-uh.

238
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:21,070
My actors are brilliant,
I merely facilitate.

239
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:21,370
JULIA:

240
00:15:21,470 --> 00:15:23,005
Carmen is one of my
friends from Yale.

241
00:15:23,105 --> 00:15:25,608
Yale. Well, I shall try not
to hold that against you.

242
00:15:25,708 --> 00:15:27,409
Welcome to the theater.
- Thanks.

243
00:15:27,509 --> 00:15:29,509
KERR: Charming.

244
00:15:32,514 --> 00:15:33,514
JULIA:

245
00:15:33,614 --> 00:15:36,263
He's like family. God,
I love this place.

246
00:15:36,363 --> 00:15:39,889
As you may have heard,
this season on the main stage...

247
00:15:39,989 --> 00:15:42,791
...we will be mounting
The Winter's Tale.

248
00:15:42,891 --> 00:15:45,655
And, as is tradition...

249
00:15:46,195 --> 00:15:49,465
...acting interns will be
assigned roles in the ensemble...

250
00:15:49,565 --> 00:15:52,557
...with the exception...

251
00:15:53,068 --> 00:15:56,401
...of one sacrificial lamb...

252
00:15:56,839 --> 00:15:58,407
Is he drunk?

253
00:15:58,507 --> 00:15:59,975
