00:50:09,189 --> 00:50:11,024
No.
- Well...

770
00:50:11,124 --> 00:50:13,954
...I'm getting in the car right now.

771
00:50:14,054 --> 00:50:16,774
Hang on. Can I
bring you anything?

772
00:50:16,997 --> 00:50:18,997
Pregnancy test?

773
00:50:22,936 --> 00:50:26,039
Lift up your countenance,
as it were the day of celebration...

774
00:50:26,139 --> 00:50:30,210
...of that nuptial which we two
have sworn shall come.

775
00:50:30,310 --> 00:50:33,473
Oh, Lady Fortune,
stand you auspicious.

776
00:50:33,647 --> 00:50:36,216
God, why don't people
talk like this anymore?

777
00:50:36,316 --> 00:50:38,316
We've gotten so lazy.

778
00:50:38,485 --> 00:50:42,356
We don't say, 'Oh, Lady Fortune,
stand you auspicious.'

779
00:50:42,456 --> 00:50:46,085
We say, 'Dear God, help me.'

780
00:50:46,259 --> 00:50:48,817
Or instead of, 'Enjoy
the honey-heavy dew...

781
00:50:48,917 --> 00:50:50,764
of slumber,' 'Yo, get some Z's.'

782
00:50:50,864 --> 00:50:52,099
It's not the same.

783
00:50:52,199 --> 00:50:56,036
It's just, it sounds so good
and it feels so good to say.

784
00:50:56,136 --> 00:50:58,661
It's rich and luscious and...

785
00:50:59,106 --> 00:51:02,872
See how she lays her cheek
upon her hand?

786
00:51:03,043 --> 00:51:05,753
Oh, that I were a glove upon that...

787
00:51:05,853 --> 00:51:08,733
hand, that I might
touch that cheek.

788
00:51:10,884 --> 00:51:12,884
See what I mean?

789
00:51:13,053 --> 00:51:15,053
Yep.

790
00:51:15,489 --> 00:51:18,369
Give me those flowers
there, Dorcas.

791
00:51:25,065 --> 00:51:27,065
Here's flowers for you.

792
00:51:27,067 --> 00:51:30,662
Hot lavender, mint, savory.

793
00:51:32,339 --> 00:51:33,974
Now...

794
00:51:34,074 --> 00:51:36,074
...my fairest friend...

795
00:51:36,376 --> 00:51:38,693
...I would I had some
flowers of the spring...

796
00:51:38,793 --> 00:51:40,647
that might become
your time of day...

797
00:51:40,747 --> 00:51:42,788
...but these I lack to
make you garlands...

798
00:51:42,888 --> 00:51:44,151
of, and, my sweet friend...

799
00:51:44,251 --> 00:51:47,243
...to strew you o'er and o'er.

800
00:51:47,954 --> 00:51:50,184
What, like a corpse?

801
00:51:50,924 --> 00:51:54,883
No. Like a bank for love,
to lie and play on...

802
00:51:55,061 --> 00:51:58,691
...not like a corpse, or
if, not to be buried,

803
00:51:58,791 --> 00:52:01,031
but quick, and in mine arms.

804
00:52:07,841 --> 00:52:09,841
Uh...

805
00:52:12,679 --> 00:52:14,943
Um, sorry, Bill.

806
00:52:15,982 --> 00:52:17,982
I forgot my line.

807
00:52:19,486 --> 00:52:23,326
Take a break.
We'll pick it up where we left off.

808
00:52:31,031 --> 00:52:33,431
Do not go to drama school.

809
00:52:34,601 --> 00:52:36,601
It'll ruin you.

810
00:52:40,440 --> 00:52:45,241
Well, thank you, Nigel.
I'm enjoying your work too. Ah.

811
00:52:46,947 --> 00:52:48,947
Carmen?

812
00:52:51,351 --> 00:52:53,351
JULIA: Let me help you.

813
00:52:57,624 --> 00:52:59,126
Did anybody see that?

814
00:52:59,226 --> 00:53:01,226
No, you're fine.
- Okay.

815
00:53:06,366 --> 00:53:08,366
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

816
00:53:12,973 --> 00:53:16,093
Guess what got here
just before you did?

817
00:53:21,581 --> 00:53:21,787
TIBBY:

818
00:53:21,887 --> 00:53:23,416
So I thought it'd
be easier that way.

819
00:53:23,516 --> 00:53:27,354
Wait. You told him
you weren't pregnant in an e-mail?

820
00:53:27,454 --> 00:53:30,894
If I had called him
or told him in person...

821
00:53:31,858 --> 00:53:33,800
...he might've thought
things could just...

822
00:53:33,900 --> 00:53:35,796
go back the way they
were, but they can't.

823
00:53:35,896 --> 00:53:38,092
Well, why not? I mean, if you're not...

824
00:53:38,192 --> 00:53:40,100
pregnant, then
what's the problem?

825
00:53:40,200 --> 00:53:42,361
I suck at relationships.

826
00:53:42,535 --> 00:53:43,670
Should've been a guy.

827
00:53:43,770 --> 00:53:46,206
No, a guy wouldn't worry about
sucking at relationships.

828
00:53:46,306 --> 00:53:48,306
[TIBBY LAUGHS]

829
00:53:49,042 --> 00:53:51,362
You know what the problem is?

830
00:53:51,578 --> 00:53:53,914
Every time I try to
get close to somebody...

831
00:53:54,014 --> 00:53:58,814
...it's like there's something
out there that just says, 'Oh.

832
00:53:59,386 --> 00:54:02,746
Tibby's about to be happy.
Better get her.'

833
00:54:07,327 --> 00:54:10,607
I'm not really sure what to say,
you know?

834
00:54:11,498 --> 00:54:13,978
Well, maybe you're just scared.

835
00:54:14,668 --> 00:54:16,668
Yeah, maybe.

836
00:54:19,339 --> 00:54:21,739
Hey, I should really get back.

837
00:54:22,242 --> 00:54:24,477
And leave me in the
middle of my life?

838
00:54:24,577 --> 00:54:26,046
God.

839
00:54:26,146 --> 00:54:28,481
I'll have another
breakdown if you stay.

840
00:54:28,581 --> 00:54:31,461
Tempting. But I have
an early class.

841
00:54:31,851 --> 00:54:33,876
Right-o.
- Come on.

842
00:54:34,254 --> 00:54:36,254
I'll walk you back.

843
00:54:43,530 --> 00:54:46,410
[WOMAN SPEAKS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]...

844
00:54:46,533 --> 00:54:49,413
[NASRIN SPEAKING IN
